{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VdRP81MNcCrT1Loxx58qMT","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# PRD: Lateral Travel — Hotel Booking Platform\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Overview\n4\t\n5\t**Feature / Project Name:** Lateral Travel (technical assessment: Booking.com-like hotel booking flow)\n6\t\n7\t**Problem Statement:**\n8\tTravelers need a fast, trustworthy way to discover hotels for a given destination and dates, judge quality via real guest feedback, and book with confidence — without friction like mandatory account creation. This PRD scopes a small but complete product slice (search → details → reviews → checkout → confirmation) that demonstrates sound product thinking and engineering quality within a 4–6 hour build.\n9\t\n10\t**Proposed Solution:**\n11\tA responsive Next.js web app where users search/filter hotels, view rich detail pages (photos, amenities, map, reviews), save favorites, and complete a guest checkout that produces a confirmed booking backed by a mocked payment step.\n12\t\n13\t**AI Build Summary:**\n14\t> Build a Next.js 16 (App Router) + React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS web app using shadcn/ui components. Use Next.js Route Handlers as the backend, backed by in-memory/JSON mock data (no database, no auth). Use Zod for shared client/server validation, react-hook-form for forms, URL search params for search state, and a small persisted Zustand store for favorites. Support hotel search with filters/sort, a hotel details page with photo gallery + map + reviews, a favorites list persisted client-side, and a checkout flow with mocked payment that returns a confirmed booking. Guest-only flows for both checkout and reviews — no login. Must include loading/empty/error states, keyboard-accessible forms, responsive layouts, and meaningful tests.\n15\t\n16\t---\n17\t\n18\t## 2. Goals & Success Metrics\n19\t\n20\t**Primary Goal:** Ship a working end-to-end booking flow (search → details → reviews → checkout → confirmation) that is functionally complete, accessible, tested, and runnable with a single command.\n21\t\n22\t**Success Metrics:**\n23\t- All 5 must-have capabilities (search, details, reviews, availability/price, checkout) work end-to-end locally.\n24\t- CI (`pnpm lint`, `pnpm test`, `pnpm build`) passes on every push/PR.\n25\t- Core flow (search to confirmed booking) completes without layout breakage at mobile (375px) and desktop widths.\n26\t\n27\t**Anti-goals:**\n28\t- Not implementing real payment processing.\n29\t- Not implementing real user accounts or persistent auth sessions.\n30\t- Not building a review moderation console — moderation is a basic stub (e.g. required fields, simple word filter).\n31\t- Not chasing pixel-perfect visual polish over functional completeness.\n32\t\n33\t---\n34\t\n35\t## 3. Scope & Constraints\n36\t\n37\t**In scope:**\n38\t- Search/browse hotels by destination, date range, guest count.\n39\t- Filtering (price range, star rating, amenities) and sorting (price, rating).\n40\t- Hotel details page: photos, amenities, description, map, live price calculation.\n41\t- Reviews: list existing reviews, submit a new review as a guest.\n42\t- Availability + price display driven by date range and guest count.\n43\t- Favorites: save/unsave hotels, view a favorites list (client-persisted, no auth).\n44\t- Checkout flow with guest contact info + mocked payment → confirmed booking.\n45\t- Backend API via Next.js Route Handlers over mocked/in-memory data.\n46\t\n47\t**Out of scope:**\n48\t- Real payment processing (Stripe/PSP integration).\n49\t- User accounts, login, persistent sessions, or cross-device sync.\n50\t- Booking modification/cancellation after confirmation.\n51\t- Email/SMS confirmation delivery.\n52\t- Admin/moderation dashboard.\n53\t- i18n / multi-currency.\n54\t- Real geocoding — hotels ship with static lat/lng in mock data.\n55\t\n56\t**Technical constraints:**\n57\t- Platform: responsive web only (desktop + mobile breakpoints).\n58\t- Auth: none — guest checkout and guest reviews only, captured via name/email per action.\n59\t- Accessibility: WCAG AA basics — labeled inputs, visible focus states, keyboard-operable flows, `aria-live` for async status.\n60\t- Offline support: not required.\n61\t- Performance: no formal budget; avoid obvious waterfalls, use loading skeletons for perceived speed.\n62\t- Data residency/compliance: none — all data is mocked, no real PII processed.\n63\t- **Repo note:** this workspace's `AGENTS.md` flags that the installed Next.js build has non-standard/breaking-change APIs relative to public docs. Whoever implements this PRD should read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing routing/data-fetching code, rather than assuming standard Next.js conventions.\n64\t\n65\t---\n66\t\n67\t## 4. Jobs to Be Done (JTBD)\n68\t\n69\t| Priority | Job Statement |\n70\t|----------|---------------|\n71\t| 1 | When planning a trip, I want to search hotels by destination and dates, so I can see what's available and compare options quickly. |\n72\t| 2 | When considering a hotel, I want to read what other guests say, so I can gauge trustworthiness before booking. |\n73\t| 3 | When browsing results, I want to see hotels on a map, so I can judge location relative to where I want to be. |\n74\t| 4 | When I've narrowed down options, I want to save favorites, so I can compare them later without losing track. |\n75\t| 5 | When I've decided, I want to complete checkout quickly as a guest, so I get a confirmed booking without creating an account. |\n76\t\n77\t---\n78\t\n79\t## 5. User Stories\n80\t\n81\t| ID  | Role | Action | Benefit | JTBD Ref |\n82\t|-----|------|--------|---------|----------|\n83\t| US1 | Traveler | search hotels by destination, dates, and guest count | I only see relevant, available options | J1 |\n84\t| US2 | Traveler | filter and sort results (price, rating, amenities) | I can narrow down to what matters to me | J1 |\n85\t| US3 | Traveler | view a hotel's details, photos, amenities, and price breakdown | I know exactly what I'm booking and for how much | J1 |\n86\t| US4 | Traveler | see a hotel's location on a map, and see all results plotted on a map | I can judge how convenient the location is | J3 |\n87\t| US5 | Traveler | read reviews on a hotel's page | I can trust the hotel before committing | J2 |\n88\t| US6 | Traveler | submit a review as a guest (name, rating, text) | I can share my experience without creating an account | J2 |\n89\t| US7 | Traveler | save/unsave a hotel as a favorite | I can keep track of options I'm considering | J4 |\n90\t| US8 | Traveler | view my list of favorited hotels | I can revisit and compare my shortlist | J4 |\n91\t| US9 | Traveler | pick dates and guest count and see live availability + price | I know the real cost before checkout | J1, J5 |\n92\t| US10 | Traveler | complete checkout with guest info and a mocked payment | I get a confirmed booking with minimal friction | J5 |\n93\t| US11 | Traveler | view a booking confirmation | I have proof and details of my reservation | J5 |\n94\t\n95\t---\n96\t\n97\t## 6. Proposed Experience\n98\t\n99\t**Design Direction:**\n100\tClean, trustworthy travel-marketplace feel (Booking.com-simplified). Sticky search bar keeps destination/dates/guests always editable. Desktop uses a split view — results list on the left, map on the right; mobile collapses to a list with a \"Map\" toggle. Card-based results emphasize photo, price, and rating at a glance.\n101\t\n102\t**Key Screens / States:**\n103\t- **Search/Results** — sticky search bar, filter sidebar, sort control, result cards (photo, name, star rating, price/night, favorite heart), map panel with pins.\n104\t- **Hotel Details** — photo gallery, name/location/rating, amenities, description, embedded map, date/guest picker with live price, reviews list + add-review form, sticky \"Reserve\" CTA.\n105\t- **Favorites** — grid of saved hotels; empty state when none saved.\n106\t- **Checkout** — booking summary (dates, guests, price breakdown), guest info form, mocked payment fields, submit.\n107\t- **Confirmation** — booking reference, summary, \"what's next\" copy.\n108\t- **Empty state:** no results match filters → message + \"reset filters\" action.\n109\t- **Error state:** API/network failure → friendly message + retry action.\n110\t- **Loading state:** skeleton cards for results/details; disabled/spinner button during checkout submit.\n111\t\n112\t**Interaction Model:**\n113\t1. Land on search/results (default: all hotels, or last search restored from URL params).\n114\t2. Adjust destination/dates/guests → debounced re-search.\n115\t3. Apply filters/sort.\n116\t4. Open a hotel → details page.\n117\t5. Adjust dates/guests, review live price, read reviews, optionally submit one.\n118\t6. Click \"Reserve\" → checkout.\n119\t7. Fill guest info + mock payment → submit.\n120\t8. Redirect to confirmation page with a booking reference.\n121\t- Favorite toggle is available anywhere a hotel card renders; it updates optimistically and persists to `localStorage` (no auth, so no cross-device sync).\n122\t\n123\t**Accessibility Notes:**\n124\t- All interactive elements keyboard-reachable with visible focus states.\n125\t- Every form input has an associated label.\n126\t- Map has a non-visual fallback (the underlying list is still navigable/readable for screen reader users; map is supplementary, not the only way to browse).\n127\t- Status messages (favorite added, review submitted, booking confirmed, errors) announced via `aria-live` regions.\n128\t- Color contrast meets WCAG AA.\n129\t\n130\t**Figma / Design Link:** Not required for this assessment; design direction is documented above.\n131\t\n132\t---\n133\t\n134\t## 7. Component Inventory\n135\t\n136\t| Component | Type | Description | Linked Stories |\n137\t|-----------|------|-------------|-----------------|\n138\t| SearchBar | Form | Destination, date-range, guest inputs; triggers search | US1 |\n139\t| FilterPanel | Form | Price range, star rating, amenity filters | US2 |\n140\t| SortDropdown | Form | Sort results by price/rating | US2 |\n141\t| HotelCard | Display | Result card: photo, name, rating, price, favorite toggle | US1, US7 |\n142\t| MapView | Display | Pins for result set, or single-hotel map on details page | US4 |\n143\t| PhotoGallery | Display | Hotel image gallery | US3 |\n144\t| AmenitiesList | Display | Icon + label list of amenities | US3 |\n145\t| ReviewList | Display | Paginated list of reviews | US5 |\n146\t| ReviewForm | Form | Add review: name, rating, text | US6 |\n147\t| FavoriteButton | Action | Heart-icon toggle, optimistic update | US7 |\n148\t| FavoritesGrid | Layout | Grid of favorited hotels + empty state | US8 |\n149\t| DateGuestPicker | Form | Date range + guest count selector, drives live price | US9 |\n150\t| PriceBreakdown | Display | Nightly rate × nights + fees = total | US9, US10 |\n151\t| CheckoutForm | Form | Guest info + mocked payment fields | US10 |\n152\t| ConfirmationSummary | Display | Booking reference + summary | US11 |\n153\t| EmptyState | Display | No results / no favorites messaging | US2, US8 |\n154\t| ErrorState | Display | API failure message + retry | all async screens |\n155\t| LoadingSkeleton | Display | Skeleton loaders for results/details/reviews | all async screens |\n156\t| Toast | Display | Transient confirmation (favorited, review submitted) | US6, US7 |\n157\t\n158\t---\n159\t\n160\t## 8. Data Models\n161\t\n162\t```typescript\n163\tinterface Hotel {\n164\t  id: string;\n165\t  name: string;\n166\t  description: string;\n167\t  destination: string;         // city/region, used for search matching\n168\t  address: string;\n169\t  lat: number;                 // static mock coordinate\n170\t  lng: number;\n171\t  starRating: number;          // 1-5\n172\t  pricePerNight: number;       // base rate, currency in cents\n173\t  currency: string;            // e.g. \"USD\"\n174\t  amenities: string[];\n175\t  photos: string[];            // image URLs\n176\t  maxGuests: number;\n177\t  reviewCount: number;         // denormalized for list sorting\n178\t  averageRating: number;       // denormalized, derived from Review[]\n179\t}\n180\t\n181\tinterface Review {\n182\t  id: string;\n183\t  hotelId: string;             // FK -> Hotel\n184\t  guestName: string;\n185\t  rating: number;              // 1-5\n186\t  text: string;\n187\t  createdAt: string;           // ISO8601\n188\t}\n189\t\n190\tinterface Booking {\n191\t  id: string;\n192\t  hotelId: string;             // FK -> Hotel\n193\t  checkIn: string;             // ISO8601 date\n194\t  checkOut: string;            // ISO8601 date\n195\t  guests: number;\n196\t  guestName: string;\n197\t  guestEmail: string;\n198\t  totalPrice: number;          // cents\n199\t  currency: string;\n200\t  status: \"confirmed\";         // only outcome in MVP (mocked payment always succeeds)\n201\t  createdAt: string;           // ISO8601\n202\t}\n203\t\n204\tinterface SearchQuery {\n205\t  destination?: string;\n206\t  checkIn?: string;            // ISO8601 date\n207\t  checkOut?: string;           // ISO8601 date\n208\t  guests?: number;\n209\t  minPrice?: number;\n210\t  maxPrice?: number;\n211\t  minRating?: number;\n212\t  amenities?: string[];\n213\t  sort?: \"price_asc\" | \"price_desc\" | \"rating_desc\";\n214\t}\n215\t```\n216\t\n217\t> Favorites are not modeled server-side in MVP — they live entirely in `localStorage` as `string[]` of `Hotel.id`, since there is no auth/user identity to key server-side favorites against.\n218\t\n219\t---\n220\t\n221\t## 9. API / Integration Surface\n222\t\n223\t| Method | Path | Description | Auth Required | Response Shape |\n224\t|--------|------|--------------|----------------|-----------------|\n225\t| GET | /api/hotels | Search/list hotels with query params (`destination`, `checkIn`, `checkOut`, `guests`, `minPrice`, `maxPrice`, `minRating`, `amenities`, `sort`) | No | `{ data: Hotel[], total: number }` |\n226\t| GET | /api/hotels/:id | Fetch a single hotel | No | `Hotel` |\n227\t| GET | /api/hotels/:id/reviews | List reviews for a hotel | No | `{ data: Review[], total: number }` |\n228\t| POST | /api/hotels/:id/reviews | Add a review (guest) | No | `Review` |\n229\t| GET | /api/hotels/:id/availability | Compute price/availability for `checkIn`, `checkOut`, `guests` | No | `{ available: boolean, nights: number, pricePerNight: number, totalPrice: number }` |\n230\t| POST | /api/bookings | Create a booking (checkout) | No | `Booking` |\n231\t| GET | /api/bookings/:id | Fetch a booking (confirmation page) | No | `Booking` |\n232\t\n233\t**External integrations:**\n234\t- Map rendering: recommend Leaflet + OpenStreetMap tiles (no API key required, fits the timebox) over Google Maps.\n235\t- Payment: mocked client-side (no real PSP call); `POST /api/bookings` always returns `status: \"confirmed\"`.\n236\t\n237\t---\n238\t\n239\t## 10. State Management Map\n240\t\n241\t| State | Location | Persistence | Notes |\n242\t|-------|----------|-------------|-------|\n243\t| Search filters (destination, dates, guests, price/rating filters, sort) | URL query params | None (shareable/bookmarkable) | Enables back-button and shareable search links |\n244\t| Hotel list / hotel detail / reviews | Server state (fetched per request) | None (re-fetched) | Backed by mocked in-memory/JSON data store |\n245\t| Favorites | Persisted Zustand store backed by `localStorage` | Persistent (per browser) | No server sync — no auth/user identity to key against |\n246\t| Checkout form (guest info, mock payment fields) | Local UI state | None until submit | Cleared/replaced by confirmation on success |\n247\t| Booking confirmation | Server state (fetched by booking id) | None (re-fetched) | Booking id passed via route param after checkout |\n248\t\n249\t---\n250\t\n251\t## 11. Technical Implementation Details\n252\t\n253\t### Tech Stack Recommendation\n254\t\n255\t| Layer | Choice | Rationale |\n256\t|-------|--------|-----------|\n257\t| Frontend | Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript strict | Already scaffolded in this repo; React 19 + strict types support a small, composable UI with good safety. |\n258\t| Styling | Tailwind CSS 4 | Already installed; fast responsive layout work with minimal custom CSS. |\n259\t| Component system | shadcn/ui + Radix primitives + lucide-react icons | Accessible, production-grade UI primitives that remain fully Tailwind-customizable. |\n260\t| Forms | react-hook-form | Low boilerplate, performant controlled/uncontrolled form handling for search, reviews, availability, and checkout. |\n261\t| Validation | Zod + `@hookform/resolvers` | Shared schema validation for route handlers and forms; response/input types can be derived with `z.infer`. |\n262\t| Backend | Next.js Route Handlers (`app/api/**/route.ts`) | Satisfies \"frontend calls a backend API\" without standing up a separate Express/Fastify service. |\n263\t| Data store | JSON seed data + in-memory mutations | No DB setup needed for a 4-6hr scope; resets on server restart are acceptable and should be documented. |\n264\t| Client state | URL search params + small persisted Zustand store | Search/filter state is shareable and bookmarkable; favorites persist locally without auth. |\n265\t| Server state | Native `fetch` from Server Components where possible | React Query is unnecessary for this small API surface; fewer dependencies and less client JS. |\n266\t| Dates/pricing | date-fns | Robust date parsing, formatting, and night-count calculation without custom date math. |\n267\t| Auth | None | Explicit product decision — guest checkout and guest reviews only. |\n268\t| Map | Leaflet + OpenStreetMap | No API key/setup friction, unlike Google Maps; map remains progressive enhancement. |\n269\t| Testing | Vitest + React Testing Library + MSW; Playwright optional | Unit/integration coverage for business logic, forms, and API contracts; one e2e happy path only if time allows. |\n270\t| CI | GitHub Actions | `pnpm lint`, `pnpm test`, and `pnpm build` on PR/push per release process requirements. |\n271\t| Hosting | Vercel | Native fit for Next.js, zero-config deploy, easy demo URL. |\n272\t| Monorepo tooling | Do not add Nx | The current repo is a small Next app; Nx would add setup overhead without assessment value. |\n273\t\n274\t### Dependencies to Add\n275\t\n276\t```bash\n277\tpnpm add zod react-hook-form @hookform/resolvers zustand date-fns lucide-react clsx tailwind-merge class-variance-authority\n278\tpnpm dlx shadcn@latest init\n279\tpnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button card input label form select slider checkbox badge separator skeleton sheet dialog calendar popover sonner\n280\tpnpm add leaflet react-leaflet\n281\tpnpm add -D vitest @vitejs/plugin-react @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom @testing-library/user-event jsdom msw @types/leaflet\n282\t```\n283\t\n284\tOptional, if the timebox allows one browser-level happy path:\n285\t\n286\t```bash\n287\tpnpm add -D @playwright/test\n288\tpnpm exec playwright install chromium\n289\t```\n290\t\n291\t### Validation Strategy\n292\t\n293\t- `search-query-schema.ts` normalizes query params and applies defaults for destination, guests, price/rating filters, amenities, and sort.\n294\t- `review-schema.ts` validates guest name, rating `1-5`, text length, and a lightweight moderation guard.\n295\t- `availability-schema.ts` validates date range and guest count before price calculation.\n296\t- `booking-schema.ts` validates hotel id, guest details, date range, guest count, and mock payment fields.\n297\t- Route handlers validate all incoming query/body data with Zod before calling data helpers.\n298\t- Forms use react-hook-form with Zod resolvers so client-side errors match server-side constraints.\n299\t\n300\t### Implementation Order\n301\t\n302\t1. Foundation: add scripts, initialize shadcn, add UI primitives, create shared types, schemas, mock data, and price helpers.\n303\t2. Backend API: implement hotel search/detail, reviews, availability, booking creation, and booking lookup route handlers.\n304\t3. Search/details: build URL-driven results, cards, filters, sort, detail page, availability, reviews, and favorites.\n305\t4. Checkout: build checkout form, submit booking, redirect to confirmation, and handle not-found/error states.\n306\t5. Quality pass: add unit/integration tests, CI workflow, README notes, responsive pass, accessibility pass, and documented trade-offs.\n307\t\n308\t### Test Plan\n309\t\n310\tMinimum coverage:\n311\t\n312\t- `filter-hotels.spec.ts`: destination, guests, price, rating, amenities, and sort.\n313\t- `pricing.spec.ts`: nights, invalid date range, max guests, and total price.\n314\t- `schemas.spec.ts`: review and booking validation.\n315\t- `checkout-form.spec.tsx`: validation, loading state, and successful submit.\n316\t- `review-form.spec.tsx`: client validation and list refresh/optimistic update.\n317\t\n318\tCI command:\n319\t\n320\t```bash\n321\tpnpm lint\n322\tpnpm test\n323\tpnpm build\n324\t```\n325\t\n326\t---\n327\t\n328\t## 12. Suggested File Structure\n329\t\n330\t```\n331\tlateral-assessment/\n332\t├── app/\n333\t│   ├── page.tsx                          # search/results (home)\n334\t│   ├── hotels/\n335\t│   │   └── [id]/\n336\t│   │       └── page.tsx                  # hotel details\n337\t│   ├── favorites/\n338\t│   │   └── page.tsx\n339\t│   ├── checkout/\n340\t│   │   ├── [hotelId]/page.tsx            # checkout form\n341\t│   │   └── confirmation/\n342\t│   │       └── [bookingId]/page.tsx\n343\t│   └── api/\n344\t│       ├── hotels/\n345\t│       │   ├── route.ts                  # GET (search/list)\n346\t│       │   └── [id]/\n347\t│       │       ├── route.ts              # GET single hotel\n348\t│       │       ├── reviews/route.ts      # GET/POST reviews\n349\t│       │       └── availability/route.ts # GET availability/price\n350\t│       └── bookings/\n351\t│           ├── route.ts                  # POST create booking\n352\t│           └── [id]/route.ts             # GET booking\n353\t├── components/\n354\t│   ├── booking/ (DateGuestPicker, PriceBreakdown, CheckoutForm, ConfirmationSummary)\n355\t│   ├── favorites/ (FavoriteButton, FavoritesGrid)\n356\t│   ├── hotels/ (HotelCard, PhotoGallery, AmenitiesList, MapView)\n357\t│   ├── reviews/ (ReviewList, ReviewForm)\n358\t│   ├── search/ (SearchBar, FilterPanel, SortDropdown)\n359\t│   ├── shared/ (EmptyState, ErrorState, LoadingSkeleton)\n360\t│   └── ui/                              # shadcn/ui primitives\n361\t├── lib/\n362\t│   ├── api/                              # typed fetch helpers where useful\n363\t│   ├── schemas/                          # Zod schemas shared by forms/routes\n364\t│   ├── stores/                           # Zustand stores, e.g. persisted favorites\n365\t│   ├── utils/                            # pricing, filtering, formatting helpers\n366\t│   ├── hotels.ts                         # mock data access + search/filter logic\n367\t│   ├── bookings.ts                       # booking creation/lookup logic\n368\t│   └── types.ts                          # shared types (Section 8 models)\n369\t├── data/\n370\t│   └── hotels.json                       # seed mock data\n371\t├── tests/\n372\t│   └── setup.ts                          # Testing Library/MSW setup\n373\t└── .github/\n374\t    └── workflows/\n375\t        └── ci.yml                        # lint + test + build\n376\t```\n377\t\n378\tRoute files should stay thin: validate request data, call `lib/` helpers, return typed JSON responses. Filtering, sorting, pricing, booking creation, and review mutation logic should live outside route handlers so it can be unit tested.\n379\t\n380\t---\n381\t\n382\t## 13. Acceptance Criteria\n383\t\n384\t**US1 — Search hotels by destination, dates, guests**\n385\t- [ ] Submitting destination + date range + guests returns only hotels matching `destination` and where `maxGuests >= guests`.\n386\t- [ ] Leaving all fields empty returns the full hotel list.\n387\t- [ ] Loading state shown while results are fetched.\n388\t- [ ] Empty state shown when zero hotels match, with a \"reset filters\" action.\n389\t- [ ] Error state shown with retry if `/api/hotels` fails.\n390\t\n391\t**US2 — Filter and sort results**\n392\t- [ ] Setting min/max price filters out hotels outside that range.\n393\t- [ ] Setting a minimum star rating filters out hotels below it.\n394\t- [ ] Selecting amenities filters to hotels containing all selected amenities.\n395\t- [ ] Sort control reorders results by price (asc/desc) or rating (desc) without a full page reload.\n396\t\n397\t**US3 — View hotel details**\n398\t- [ ] Details page renders name, address, star rating, description, amenities, and photo gallery for a valid `:id`.\n399\t- [ ] Requesting an invalid/nonexistent `:id` shows a not-found state, not a crash.\n400\t- [ ] Price breakdown reflects current date range and guest count.\n401\t\n402\t**US4 — Map view**\n403\t- [ ] Results page shows a map with a pin per visible result; clicking a pin highlights/scrolls to the matching card.\n404\t- [ ] Hotel details page shows a single-pin map at the hotel's location.\n405\t- [ ] Map failing to load does not block viewing the list/details content.\n406\t\n407\t**US5 — Read reviews**\n408\t- [ ] Hotel details page lists all reviews for that hotel with guest name, rating, text, and date.\n409\t- [ ] Hotel with zero reviews shows an empty state, not a broken list.\n410\t\n411\t**US6 — Submit a review**\n412\t- [ ] Submitting a review with name, rating (1-5), and text creates it via `POST /api/hotels/:id/reviews` and it appears in the list without a full page reload.\n413\t- [ ] Submitting with a missing required field is blocked client-side with a visible validation message.\n414\t- [ ] Submitted review updates the hotel's `averageRating`/`reviewCount`.\n415\t\n416\t**US7 — Favorite/unfavorite a hotel**\n417\t- [ ] Clicking the heart on any hotel card toggles favorited state immediately (optimistic).\n418\t- [ ] Favorited state persists across page reloads via `localStorage`.\n419\t- [ ] Favorite state is consistent between the results list and the details page for the same hotel.\n420\t\n421\t**US8 — View favorites list**\n422\t- [ ] Favorites page lists all hotels currently saved in `localStorage`.\n423\t- [ ] Favorites page shows an empty state with a link back to search when none are saved.\n424\t- [ ] Unfavoriting from the favorites page removes it from the grid immediately.\n425\t\n426\t**US9 — Live availability + price**\n427\t- [ ] Changing check-in/check-out dates or guest count on the details page recalculates and displays nights × rate = total.\n428\t- [ ] Guest count exceeding `maxGuests` is blocked with an inline message.\n429\t- [ ] Invalid date range (checkout before/equal to checkin) is blocked with an inline message.\n430\t\n431\t**US10 — Checkout**\n432\t- [ ] Checkout form requires guest name, email, and mock payment fields before submission is enabled.\n433\t- [ ] Submitting valid checkout calls `POST /api/bookings` and, on success, redirects to the confirmation page for the new booking id.\n434\t- [ ] Submit button shows a loading/disabled state while the request is in flight.\n435\t- [ ] A failed booking request shows an error message and does not navigate away.\n436\t\n437\t**US11 — Booking confirmation**\n438\t- [ ] Confirmation page fetches and displays the booking by id: hotel name, dates, guests, total price, and a booking reference.\n439\t- [ ] Navigating directly to a confirmation URL for a nonexistent booking id shows a not-found state, not a crash.\n440\t\n441\t---\n442\t\n443\t## 14. Open Questions & Risks\n444\t\n445\t- **Q:** Should review submission have any spam/abuse protection beyond required fields? — *Owner: PM.* Recommendation: skip for MVP, note as Phase 2 (basic moderation flag).\n446\t- **Q:** Should favorites ever sync server-side (e.g. keyed by a generated device/session id) to survive `localStorage` clears? — *Owner: PM.* Recommendation: no, out of scope given no-auth decision.\n447\t- **Risk:** Repo's `AGENTS.md` indicates the installed Next.js version has non-standard/breaking APIs vs. public docs — implementation could stall on unfamiliar routing/data-fetching conventions. *Mitigation:* read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before starting implementation, not mid-build.\n448\t- **Risk:** In-memory mock data resets on every server restart, including new bookings/reviews. *Mitigation:* acceptable for assessment scope; document clearly in README as a known limitation.\n449\t- **Tradeoff:** No auth simplifies scope significantly but means favorites/bookings aren't portable across devices — explicitly accepted per product decision.\n450\t\n451\t---\n452\t\n453\t## 15. Rollout & Next Steps\n454\t\n455\t**MVP scope:**\n456\t- Includes: search/filter/sort, hotel details with map, reviews (list + add), favorites (localStorage), full checkout → confirmation flow, all backed by mocked API + in-memory data.\n457\t- Excludes: real payments, real auth, booking modification/cancellation, email delivery, admin/moderation tooling, i18n.\n458\t\n459\t**Phase 2+ ideas:**\n460\t- Real auth + persistent, cross-device favorites and booking history.\n461\t- Real payment integration (Stripe test mode).\n462\t- Booking modification/cancellation flow.\n463\t- Email confirmation delivery.\n464\t- Basic review moderation (flagging, profanity filter).\n465\t- Personalized recommendations based on search/favorite history.\n466\t\n467\t**Sign-off needed from:**\n468\t- [ ] PM\n469\t- [ ] Engineering lead\n470\t\n471\t**Next steps:**\n472\t1. Initialize shadcn/ui, form/validation dependencies, test tooling, and shared project scripts — *Owner: Eng.*\n473\t2. Seed mock hotel/review data (`data/hotels.json`) and shared Zod schemas — *Owner: Eng.*\n474\t3. Scaffold API route handlers per Section 9 — *Owner: Eng.*\n475\t4. Build search/results page, then details, then checkout, then confirmation, in that order (matches JTBD priority) — *Owner: Eng.*\n476\t5. Add unit/integration tests per Section 13 acceptance criteria — *Owner: Eng.*\n477\t6. Wire up GitHub Actions CI (`pnpm lint`, `pnpm test`, `pnpm build`) — *Owner: Eng.*\n478\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1a46cfe3-edd5-47d3-88ea-9b5bc1fd0648","uuid":"a2f7a1b4-2e47-4b11-bf0f-e6f3f6c54d04","timestamp":"2026-07-02T15:06:17.734Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/rensknoors/repos/lateral-assessment/docs/PRD.md","content":"# PRD: Lateral Travel — Hotel Booking Platform\n\n## 1. Overview\n\n**Feature / Project Name:** Lateral Travel (technical assessment: Booking.com-like hotel booking flow)\n\n**Problem Statement:**\nTravelers need a fast, trustworthy way to discover hotels for a given destination and dates, judge quality via real guest feedback, and book with confidence — without friction like mandatory account creation. This PRD scopes a small but complete product slice (search → details → reviews → checkout → confirmation) that demonstrates sound product thinking and engineering quality within a 4–6 hour build.\n\n**Proposed Solution:**\nA responsive Next.js web app where users search/filter hotels, view rich detail pages (photos, amenities, map, reviews), save favorites, and complete a guest checkout that produces a confirmed booking backed by a mocked payment step.\n\n**AI Build Summary:**\n> Build a Next.js 16 (App Router) + React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS web app using shadcn/ui components. Use Next.js Route Handlers as the backend, backed by in-memory/JSON mock data (no database, no auth). Use Zod for shared client/server validation, react-hook-form for forms, URL search params for search state, and a small persisted Zustand store for favorites. Support hotel search with filters/sort, a hotel details page with photo gallery + map + reviews, a favorites list persisted client-side, and a checkout flow with mocked payment that returns a confirmed booking. Guest-only flows for both checkout and reviews — no login. Must include loading/empty/error states, keyboard-accessible forms, responsive layouts, and meaningful tests.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Goals & Success Metrics\n\n**Primary Goal:** Ship a working end-to-end booking flow (search → details → reviews → checkout → confirmation) that is functionally complete, accessible, tested, and runnable with a single command.\n\n**Success Metrics:**\n- All 5 must-have capabilities (search, details, reviews, availability/price, checkout) work end-to-end locally.\n- CI (`pnpm lint`, `pnpm test`, `pnpm build`) passes on every push/PR.\n- Core flow (search to confirmed booking) completes without layout breakage at mobile (375px) and desktop widths.\n\n**Anti-goals:**\n- Not implementing real payment processing.\n- Not implementing real user accounts or persistent auth sessions.\n- Not building a review moderation console — moderation is a basic stub (e.g. required fields, simple word filter).\n- Not chasing pixel-perfect visual polish over functional completeness.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Scope & Constraints\n\n**In scope:**\n- Search/browse hotels by destination, date range, guest count.\n- Filtering (price range, star rating, amenities) and sorting (price, rating).\n- Hotel details page: photos, amenities, description, map, live price calculation.\n- Reviews: list existing reviews, submit a new review as a guest.\n- Availability + price display driven by date range and guest count.\n- Favorites: save/unsave hotels, view a favorites list (client-persisted, no auth).\n- Checkout flow with guest contact info + mocked payment → confirmed booking.\n- Backend API via Next.js Route Handlers over mocked/in-memory data.\n\n**Out of scope:**\n- Real payment processing (Stripe/PSP integration).\n- User accounts, login, persistent sessions, or cross-device sync.\n- Booking modification/cancellation after confirmation.\n- Email/SMS confirmation delivery.\n- Admin/moderation dashboard.\n- i18n / multi-currency.\n- Real geocoding — hotels ship with static lat/lng in mock data.\n\n**Technical constraints:**\n- Platform: responsive web only (desktop + mobile breakpoints).\n- Auth: none — guest checkout and guest reviews only, captured via name/email per action.\n- Accessibility: WCAG AA basics — labeled inputs, visible focus states, keyboard-operable flows, `aria-live` for async status.\n- Offline support: not required.\n- Performance: no formal budget; avoid obvious waterfalls, use loading skeletons for perceived speed.\n- Data residency/compliance: none — all data is mocked, no real PII processed.\n- **Repo note:** this workspace's `AGENTS.md` flags that the installed Next.js build has non-standard/breaking-change APIs relative to public docs. Whoever implements this PRD should read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing routing/data-fetching code, rather than assuming standard Next.js conventions.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Jobs to Be Done (JTBD)\n\n| Priority | Job Statement |\n|----------|---------------|\n| 1 | When planning a trip, I want to search hotels by destination and dates, so I can see what's available and compare options quickly. |\n| 2 | When considering a hotel, I want to read what other guests say, so I can gauge trustworthiness before booking. |\n| 3 | When browsing results, I want to see hotels on a map, so I can judge location relative to where I want to be. |\n| 4 | When I've narrowed down options, I want to save favorites, so I can compare them later without losing track. |\n| 5 | When I've decided, I want to complete checkout quickly as a guest, so I get a confirmed booking without creating an account. |\n\n---\n\n## 5. User Stories\n\n| ID  | Role | Action | Benefit | JTBD Ref |\n|-----|------|--------|---------|----------|\n| US1 | Traveler | search hotels by destination, dates, and guest count | I only see relevant, available options | J1 |\n| US2 | Traveler | filter and sort results (price, rating, amenities) | I can narrow down to what matters to me | J1 |\n| US3 | Traveler | view a hotel's details, photos, amenities, and price breakdown | I know exactly what I'm booking and for how much | J1 |\n| US4 | Traveler | see a hotel's location on a map, and see all results plotted on a map | I can judge how convenient the location is | J3 |\n| US5 | Traveler | read reviews on a hotel's page | I can trust the hotel before committing | J2 |\n| US6 | Traveler | submit a review as a guest (name, rating, text) | I can share my experience without creating an account | J2 |\n| US7 | Traveler | save/unsave a hotel as a favorite | I can keep track of options I'm considering | J4 |\n| US8 | Traveler | view my list of favorited hotels | I can revisit and compare my shortlist | J4 |\n| US9 | Traveler | pick dates and guest count and see live availability + price | I know the real cost before checkout | J1, J5 |\n| US10 | Traveler | complete checkout with guest info and a mocked payment | I get a confirmed booking with minimal friction | J5 |\n| US11 | Traveler | view a booking confirmation | I have proof and details of my reservation | J5 |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Proposed Experience\n\n**Design Direction:**\nClean, trustworthy travel-marketplace feel (Booking.com-simplified). Sticky search bar keeps destination/dates/guests always editable. Desktop uses a split view — results list on the left, map on the right; mobile collapses to a list with a \"Map\" toggle. Card-based results emphasize photo, price, and rating at a glance.\n\n**Key Screens / States:**\n- **Search/Results** — sticky search bar, filter sidebar, sort control, result cards (photo, name, star rating, price/night, favorite heart), map panel with pins.\n- **Hotel Details** — photo gallery, name/location/rating, amenities, description, embedded map, date/guest picker with live price, reviews list + add-review form, sticky \"Reserve\" CTA.\n- **Favorites** — grid of saved hotels; empty state when none saved.\n- **Checkout** — booking summary (dates, guests, price breakdown), guest info form, mocked payment fields, submit.\n- **Confirmation** — booking reference, summary, \"what's next\" copy.\n- **Empty state:** no results match filters → message + \"reset filters\" action.\n- **Error state:** API/network failure → friendly message + retry action.\n- **Loading state:** skeleton cards for results/details; disabled/spinner button during checkout submit.\n\n**Interaction Model:**\n1. Land on search/results (default: all hotels, or last search restored from URL params).\n2. Adjust destination/dates/guests → debounced re-search.\n3. Apply filters/sort.\n4. Open a hotel → details page.\n5. Adjust dates/guests, review live price, read reviews, optionally submit one.\n6. Click \"Reserve\" → checkout.\n7. Fill guest info + mock payment → submit.\n8. Redirect to confirmation page with a booking reference.\n- Favorite toggle is available anywhere a hotel card renders; it updates optimistically and persists to `localStorage` (no auth, so no cross-device sync).\n\n**Accessibility Notes:**\n- All interactive elements keyboard-reachable with visible focus states.\n- Every form input has an associated label.\n- Map has a non-visual fallback (the underlying list is still navigable/readable for screen reader users; map is supplementary, not the only way to browse).\n- Status messages (favorite added, review submitted, booking confirmed, errors) announced via `aria-live` regions.\n- Color contrast meets WCAG AA.\n\n**Figma / Design Link:** Not required for this assessment; design direction is documented above.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Component Inventory\n\n| Component | Type | Description | Linked Stories |\n|-----------|------|-------------|-----------------|\n| SearchBar | Form | Destination, date-range, guest inputs; triggers search | US1 |\n| FilterPanel | Form | Price range, star rating, amenity filters | US2 |\n| SortDropdown | Form | Sort results by price/rating | US2 |\n| HotelCard | Display | Result card: photo, name, rating, price, favorite toggle | US1, US7 |\n| MapView | Display | Pins for result set, or single-hotel map on details page | US4 |\n| PhotoGallery | Display | Hotel image gallery | US3 |\n| AmenitiesList | Display | Icon + label list of amenities | US3 |\n| ReviewList | Display | Paginated list of reviews | US5 |\n| ReviewForm | Form | Add review: name, rating, text | US6 |\n| FavoriteButton | Action | Heart-icon toggle, optimistic update | US7 |\n| FavoritesGrid | Layout | Grid of favorited hotels + empty state | US8 |\n| DateGuestPicker | Form | Date range + guest count selector, drives live price | US9 |\n| PriceBreakdown | Display | Nightly rate × nights + fees = total | US9, US10 |\n| CheckoutForm | Form | Guest info + mocked payment fields | US10 |\n| ConfirmationSummary | Display | Booking reference + summary | US11 |\n| EmptyState | Display | No results / no favorites messaging | US2, US8 |\n| ErrorState | Display | API failure message + retry | all async screens |\n| LoadingSkeleton | Display | Skeleton loaders for results/details/reviews | all async screens |\n| Toast | Display | Transient confirmation (favorited, review submitted) | US6, US7 |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Data Models\n\n```typescript\ninterface Hotel {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  description: string;\n  destination: string;         // city/region, used for search matching\n  address: string;\n  lat: number;                 // static mock coordinate\n  lng: number;\n  starRating: number;          // 1-5\n  pricePerNight: number;       // base rate, currency in cents\n  currency: string;            // e.g. \"USD\"\n  amenities: string[];\n  photos: string[];            // image URLs\n  maxGuests: number;\n  reviewCount: number;         // denormalized for list sorting\n  averageRating: number;       // denormalized, derived from Review[]\n}\n\ninterface Review {\n  id: string;\n  hotelId: string;             // FK -> Hotel\n  guestName: string;\n  rating: number;              // 1-5\n  text: string;\n  createdAt: string;           // ISO8601\n}\n\ninterface Booking {\n  id: string;\n  hotelId: string;             // FK -> Hotel\n  checkIn: string;             // ISO8601 date\n  checkOut: string;            // ISO8601 date\n  guests: number;\n  guestName: string;\n  guestEmail: string;\n  totalPrice: number;          // cents\n  currency: string;\n  status: \"confirmed\";         // only outcome in MVP (mocked payment always succeeds)\n  createdAt: string;           // ISO8601\n}\n\ninterface SearchQuery {\n  destination?: string;\n  checkIn?: string;            // ISO8601 date\n  checkOut?: string;           // ISO8601 date\n  guests?: number;\n  minPrice?: number;\n  maxPrice?: number;\n  minRating?: number;\n  amenities?: string[];\n  sort?: \"price_asc\" | \"price_desc\" | \"rating_desc\";\n}\n```\n\n> Favorites are not modeled server-side in MVP — they live entirely in `localStorage` as `string[]` of `Hotel.id`, since there is no auth/user identity to key server-side favorites against.\n\n---\n\n## 9. API / Integration Surface\n\n| Method | Path | Description | Auth Required | Response Shape |\n|--------|------|--------------|----------------|-----------------|\n| GET | /api/hotels | Search/list hotels with query params (`destination`, `checkIn`, `checkOut`, `guests`, `minPrice`, `maxPrice`, `minRating`, `amenities`, `sort`) | No | `{ data: Hotel[], total: number }` |\n| GET | /api/hotels/:id | Fetch a single hotel | No | `Hotel` |\n| GET | /api/hotels/:id/reviews | List reviews for a hotel | No | `{ data: Review[], total: number }` |\n| POST | /api/hotels/:id/reviews | Add a review (guest) | No | `Review` |\n| GET | /api/hotels/:id/availability | Compute price/availability for `checkIn`, `checkOut`, `guests` | No | `{ available: boolean, nights: number, pricePerNight: number, totalPrice: number }` |\n| POST | /api/bookings | Create a booking (checkout) | No | `Booking` |\n| GET | /api/bookings/:id | Fetch a booking (confirmation page) | No | `Booking` |\n\n**External integrations:**\n- Map rendering: recommend Leaflet + OpenStreetMap tiles (no API key required, fits the timebox) over Google Maps.\n- Payment: mocked client-side (no real PSP call); `POST /api/bookings` always returns `status: \"confirmed\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 10. State Management Map\n\n| State | Location | Persistence | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------------|-------|\n| Search filters (destination, dates, guests, price/rating filters, sort) | URL query params | None (shareable/bookmarkable) | Enables back-button and shareable search links |\n| Hotel list / hotel detail / reviews | Server state (fetched per request) | None (re-fetched) | Backed by mocked in-memory/JSON data store |\n| Favorites | Persisted Zustand store backed by `localStorage` | Persistent (per browser) | No server sync — no auth/user identity to key against |\n| Checkout form (guest info, mock payment fields) | Local UI state | None until submit | Cleared/replaced by confirmation on success |\n| Booking confirmation | Server state (fetched by booking id) | None (re-fetched) | Booking id passed via route param after checkout |\n\n---\n\n## 11. Technical Implementation Details\n\n### Tech Stack Recommendation\n\n| Layer | Choice | Rationale |\n|-------|--------|-----------|\n| Frontend | Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript strict | Already scaffolded in this repo; React 19 + strict types support a small, composable UI with good safety. |\n| Styling | Tailwind CSS 4 | Already installed; fast responsive layout work with minimal custom CSS. |\n| Component system | shadcn/ui + Radix primitives + lucide-react icons | Accessible, production-grade UI primitives that remain fully Tailwind-customizable. |\n| Forms | react-hook-form | Low boilerplate, performant controlled/uncontrolled form handling for search, reviews, availability, and checkout. |\n| Validation | Zod + `@hookform/resolvers` | Shared schema validation for route handlers and forms; response/input types can be derived with `z.infer`. |\n| Backend | Next.js Route Handlers (`app/api/**/route.ts`) | Satisfies \"frontend calls a backend API\" without standing up a separate Express/Fastify service. |\n| Data store | JSON seed data + in-memory mutations | No DB setup needed for a 4-6hr scope; resets on server restart are acceptable and should be documented. |\n| Client state | URL search params + small persisted Zustand store | Search/filter state is shareable and bookmarkable; favorites persist locally without auth. |\n| Server state | Native `fetch` from Server Components where possible | React Query is unnecessary for this small API surface; fewer dependencies and less client JS. |\n| Dates/pricing | date-fns | Robust date parsing, formatting, and night-count calculation without custom date math. |\n| Auth | None | Explicit product decision — guest checkout and guest reviews only. |\n| Map | Leaflet + OpenStreetMap | No API key/setup friction, unlike Google Maps; map remains progressive enhancement. |\n| Testing | Vitest + React Testing Library + MSW; Playwright optional | Unit/integration coverage for business logic, forms, and API contracts; one e2e happy path only if time allows. |\n| CI | GitHub Actions | `pnpm lint`, `pnpm test`, and `pnpm build` on PR/push per release process requirements. |\n| Hosting | Vercel | Native fit for Next.js, zero-config deploy, easy demo URL. |\n| Monorepo tooling | Do not add Nx | The current repo is a small Next app; Nx would add setup overhead without assessment value. |\n\n### Dependencies to Add\n\n```bash\npnpm add zod react-hook-form @hookform/resolvers zustand date-fns lucide-react clsx tailwind-merge class-variance-authority\npnpm dlx shadcn@latest init\npnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button card input label form select slider checkbox badge separator skeleton sheet dialog calendar popover sonner\npnpm add leaflet react-leaflet\npnpm add -D vitest @vitejs/plugin-react @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom @testing-library/user-event jsdom msw @types/leaflet\n```\n\nOptional, if the timebox allows one browser-level happy path:\n\n```bash\npnpm add -D @playwright/test\npnpm exec playwright install chromium\n```\n\n### Validation Strategy\n\n- `search-query-schema.ts` normalizes query params and applies defaults for destination, guests, price/rating filters, amenities, and sort.\n- `review-schema.ts` validates guest name, rating `1-5`, text length, and a lightweight moderation guard.\n- `availability-schema.ts` validates date range and guest count before price calculation.\n- `booking-schema.ts` validates hotel id, guest details, date range, guest count, and mock payment fields.\n- Route handlers validate all incoming query/body data with Zod before calling data helpers.\n- Forms use react-hook-form with Zod resolvers so client-side errors match server-side constraints.\n\n### Implementation Order\n\n1. Foundation: add scripts, initialize shadcn, add UI primitives, create shared types, schemas, mock data, and price helpers.\n2. Backend API: implement hotel search/detail, reviews, availability, booking creation, and booking lookup route handlers.\n3. Search/details: build URL-driven results, cards, filters, sort, detail page, availability, reviews, and favorites.\n4. Checkout: build checkout form, submit booking, redirect to confirmation, and handle not-found/error states.\n5. Quality pass: add unit/integration tests, CI workflow, README notes, responsive pass, accessibility pass, and documented trade-offs.\n\n### Test Plan\n\nMinimum coverage:\n\n- `filter-hotels.spec.ts`: destination, guests, price, rating, amenities, and sort.\n- `pricing.spec.ts`: nights, invalid date range, max guests, and total price.\n- `schemas.spec.ts`: review and booking validation.\n- `checkout-form.spec.tsx`: validation, loading state, and successful submit.\n- `review-form.spec.tsx`: client validation and list refresh/optimistic update.\n\nCI command:\n\n```bash\npnpm lint\npnpm test\npnpm build\n```\n\n---\n\n## 12. Suggested File Structure\n\n```\nlateral-assessment/\n├── app/\n│   ├── page.tsx                          # search/results (home)\n│   ├── hotels/\n│   │   └── [id]/\n│   │       └── page.tsx                  # hotel details\n│   ├── favorites/\n│   │   └── page.tsx\n│   ├── checkout/\n│   │   ├── [hotelId]/page.tsx            # checkout form\n│   │   └── confirmation/\n│   │       └── [bookingId]/page.tsx\n│   └── api/\n│       ├── hotels/\n│       │   ├── route.ts                  # GET (search/list)\n│       │   └── [id]/\n│       │       ├── route.ts              # GET single hotel\n│       │       ├── reviews/route.ts      # GET/POST reviews\n│       │       └── availability/route.ts # GET availability/price\n│       └── bookings/\n│           ├── route.ts                  # POST create booking\n│           └── [id]/route.ts             # GET booking\n├── components/\n│   ├── booking/ (DateGuestPicker, PriceBreakdown, CheckoutForm, ConfirmationSummary)\n│   ├── favorites/ (FavoriteButton, FavoritesGrid)\n│   ├── hotels/ (HotelCard, PhotoGallery, AmenitiesList, MapView)\n│   ├── reviews/ (ReviewList, ReviewForm)\n│   ├── search/ (SearchBar, FilterPanel, SortDropdown)\n│   ├── shared/ (EmptyState, ErrorState, LoadingSkeleton)\n│   └── ui/                              # shadcn/ui primitives\n├── lib/\n│   ├── api/                              # typed fetch helpers where useful\n│   ├── schemas/                          # Zod schemas shared by forms/routes\n│   ├── stores/                           # Zustand stores, e.g. persisted favorites\n│   ├── utils/                            # pricing, filtering, formatting helpers\n│   ├── hotels.ts                         # mock data access + search/filter logic\n│   ├── bookings.ts                       # booking creation/lookup logic\n│   └── types.ts                          # shared types (Section 8 models)\n├── data/\n│   └── hotels.json                       # seed mock data\n├── tests/\n│   └── setup.ts                          # Testing Library/MSW setup\n└── .github/\n    └── workflows/\n        └── ci.yml                        # lint + test + build\n```\n\nRoute files should stay thin: validate request data, call `lib/` helpers, return typed JSON responses. Filtering, sorting, pricing, booking creation, and review mutation logic should live outside route handlers so it can be unit tested.\n\n---\n\n## 13. Acceptance Criteria\n\n**US1 — Search hotels by destination, dates, guests**\n- [ ] Submitting destination + date range + guests returns only hotels matching `destination` and where `maxGuests >= guests`.\n- [ ] Leaving all fields empty returns the full hotel list.\n- [ ] Loading state shown while results are fetched.\n- [ ] Empty state shown when zero hotels match, with a \"reset filters\" action.\n- [ ] Error state shown with retry if `/api/hotels` fails.\n\n**US2 — Filter and sort results**\n- [ ] Setting min/max price filters out hotels outside that range.\n- [ ] Setting a minimum star rating filters out hotels below it.\n- [ ] Selecting amenities filters to hotels containing all selected amenities.\n- [ ] Sort control reorders results by price (asc/desc) or rating (desc) without a full page reload.\n\n**US3 — View hotel details**\n- [ ] Details page renders name, address, star rating, description, amenities, and photo gallery for a valid `:id`.\n- [ ] Requesting an invalid/nonexistent `:id` shows a not-found state, not a crash.\n- [ ] Price breakdown reflects current date range and guest count.\n\n**US4 — Map view**\n- [ ] Results page shows a map with a pin per visible result; clicking a pin highlights/scrolls to the matching card.\n- [ ] Hotel details page shows a single-pin map at the hotel's location.\n- [ ] Map failing to load does not block viewing the list/details content.\n\n**US5 — Read reviews**\n- [ ] Hotel details page lists all reviews for that hotel with guest name, rating, text, and date.\n- [ ] Hotel with zero reviews shows an empty state, not a broken list.\n\n**US6 — Submit a review**\n- [ ] Submitting a review with name, rating (1-5), and text creates it via `POST /api/hotels/:id/reviews` and it appears in the list without a full page reload.\n- [ ] Submitting with a missing required field is blocked client-side with a visible validation message.\n- [ ] Submitted review updates the hotel's `averageRating`/`reviewCount`.\n\n**US7 — Favorite/unfavorite a hotel**\n- [ ] Clicking the heart on any hotel card toggles favorited state immediately (optimistic).\n- [ ] Favorited state persists across page reloads via `localStorage`.\n- [ ] Favorite state is consistent between the results list and the details page for the same hotel.\n\n**US8 — View favorites list**\n- [ ] Favorites page lists all hotels currently saved in `localStorage`.\n- [ ] Favorites page shows an empty state with a link back to search when none are saved.\n- [ ] Unfavoriting from the favorites page removes it from the grid immediately.\n\n**US9 — Live availability + price**\n- [ ] Changing check-in/check-out dates or guest count on the details page recalculates and displays nights × rate = total.\n- [ ] Guest count exceeding `maxGuests` is blocked with an inline message.\n- [ ] Invalid date range (checkout before/equal to checkin) is blocked with an inline message.\n\n**US10 — Checkout**\n- [ ] Checkout form requires guest name, email, and mock payment fields before submission is enabled.\n- [ ] Submitting valid checkout calls `POST /api/bookings` and, on success, redirects to the confirmation page for the new booking id.\n- [ ] Submit button shows a loading/disabled state while the request is in flight.\n- [ ] A failed booking request shows an error message and does not navigate away.\n\n**US11 — Booking confirmation**\n- [ ] Confirmation page fetches and displays the booking by id: hotel name, dates, guests, total price, and a booking reference.\n- [ ] Navigating directly to a confirmation URL for a nonexistent booking id shows a not-found state, not a crash.\n\n---\n\n## 14. Open Questions & Risks\n\n- **Q:** Should review submission have any spam/abuse protection beyond required fields? — *Owner: PM.* Recommendation: skip for MVP, note as Phase 2 (basic moderation flag).\n- **Q:** Should favorites ever sync server-side (e.g. keyed by a generated device/session id) to survive `localStorage` clears? — *Owner: PM.* Recommendation: no, out of scope given no-auth decision.\n- **Risk:** Repo's `AGENTS.md` indicates the installed Next.js version has non-standard/breaking APIs vs. public docs — implementation could stall on unfamiliar routing/data-fetching conventions. *Mitigation:* read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before starting implementation, not mid-build.\n- **Risk:** In-memory mock data resets on every server restart, including new bookings/reviews. *Mitigation:* acceptable for assessment scope; document clearly in README as a known limitation.\n- **Tradeoff:** No auth simplifies scope significantly but means favorites/bookings aren't portable across devices — explicitly accepted per product decision.\n\n---\n\n## 15. Rollout & Next Steps\n\n**MVP scope:**\n- Includes: search/filter/sort, hotel details with map, reviews (list + add), favorites (localStorage), full checkout → confirmation flow, all backed by mocked API + in-memory data.\n- Excludes: real payments, real auth, booking modification/cancellation, email delivery, admin/moderation tooling, i18n.\n\n**Phase 2+ ideas:**\n- Real auth + persistent, cross-device favorites and booking history.\n- Real payment integration (Stripe test mode).\n- Booking modification/cancellation flow.\n- Email confirmation delivery.\n- Basic review moderation (flagging, profanity filter).\n- Personalized recommendations based on search/favorite history.\n\n**Sign-off needed from:**\n- [ ] PM\n- [ ] Engineering lead\n\n**Next steps:**\n1. Initialize shadcn/ui, form/validation dependencies, test tooling, and shared project scripts — *Owner: Eng.*\n2. Seed mock hotel/review data (`data/hotels.json`) and shared Zod schemas — *Owner: Eng.*\n3. Scaffold API route handlers per Section 9 — *Owner: Eng.*\n4. Build search/results page, then details, then checkout, then confirmation, in that order (matches JTBD priority) — *Owner: Eng.*\n5. Add unit/integration tests per Section 13 acceptance criteria — *Owner: Eng.*\n6. Wire up GitHub Actions CI (`pnpm lint`, `pnpm test`, `pnpm build`) — *Owner: Eng.*\n","numLines":478,"startLine":1,"totalLines":478}}}
