{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AcfFWoeiVsZY1SxiT88GR2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Ralph Fix Plan\n2\t\n3\t## High Priority\n4\t- [ ] Submitting destination + date range + guests returns only hotels matching `destination` and where `maxGuests >= guests`.\n5\t- [ ] Leaving all fields empty returns the full hotel list.\n6\t- [ ] Loading state shown while results are fetched.\n7\t- [ ] Empty state shown when zero hotels match, with a \"reset filters\" action.\n8\t- [ ] Error state shown with retry if `/api/hotels` fails.\n9\t- [ ] Setting min/max price filters out hotels outside that range.\n10\t- [ ] Setting a minimum star rating filters out hotels below it.\n11\t- [ ] Selecting amenities filters to hotels containing all selected amenities.\n12\t- [ ] Sort control reorders results by price (asc/desc) or rating (desc) without a full page reload.\n13\t- [ ] Details page renders name, address, star rating, description, amenities, and photo gallery for a valid `:id`.\n14\t- [ ] Requesting an invalid/nonexistent `:id` shows a not-found state, not a crash.\n15\t- [ ] Price breakdown reflects current date range and guest count.\n16\t- [ ] Results page shows a map with a pin per visible result; clicking a pin highlights/scrolls to the matching card.\n17\t- [ ] Hotel details page shows a single-pin map at the hotel's location.\n18\t- [ ] Map failing to load does not block viewing the list/details content.\n19\t- [ ] Hotel details page lists all reviews for that hotel with guest name, rating, text, and date.\n20\t- [ ] Hotel with zero reviews shows an empty state, not a broken list.\n21\t- [ ] Submitting a review with name, rating (1-5), and text creates it via `POST /api/hotels/:id/reviews` and it appears in the list without a full page reload.\n22\t- [ ] Submitting with a missing required field is blocked client-side with a visible validation message.\n23\t- [ ] Submitted review updates the hotel's `averageRating`/`reviewCount`.\n24\t- [ ] Clicking the heart on any hotel card toggles favorited state immediately (optimistic).\n25\t- [ ] Favorited state persists across page reloads via `localStorage`.\n26\t- [ ] Favorite state is consistent between the results list and the details page for the same hotel.\n27\t- [ ] Favorites page lists all hotels currently saved in `localStorage`.\n28\t- [ ] Favorites page shows an empty state with a link back to search when none are saved.\n29\t- [ ] Unfavoriting from the favorites page removes it from the grid immediately.\n30\t- [ ] Changing check-in/check-out dates or guest count on the details page recalculates and displays nights × rate = total.\n31\t- [ ] Guest count exceeding `maxGuests` is blocked with an inline message.\n32\t- [ ] Invalid date range (checkout before/equal to checkin) is blocked with an inline message.\n33\t- [ ] Checkout form requires guest name, email, and mock payment fields before submission is enabled.\n34\t\n35\t\n36\t## Medium Priority\n37\t\n38\t\n39\t## Low Priority\n40\t\n41\t\n42\t## Completed\n43\t- [x] Project enabled for Ralph\n44\t\n45\t## Notes\n46\t- Focus on MVP functionality first\n47\t- Ensure each feature is properly tested\n48\t- Update this file after each major milestone\n49\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1a46cfe3-edd5-47d3-88ea-9b5bc1fd0648","uuid":"f852f76f-3252-42e4-a537-230be0cb9503","timestamp":"2026-07-02T15:06:26.372Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/rensknoors/repos/lateral-assessment/.ralph/fix_plan.md","content":"# Ralph Fix Plan\n\n## High Priority\n- [ ] Submitting destination + date range + guests returns only hotels matching `destination` and where `maxGuests >= guests`.\n- [ ] Leaving all fields empty returns the full hotel list.\n- [ ] Loading state shown while results are fetched.\n- [ ] Empty state shown when zero hotels match, with a \"reset filters\" action.\n- [ ] Error state shown with retry if `/api/hotels` fails.\n- [ ] Setting min/max price filters out hotels outside that range.\n- [ ] Setting a minimum star rating filters out hotels below it.\n- [ ] Selecting amenities filters to hotels containing all selected amenities.\n- [ ] Sort control reorders results by price (asc/desc) or rating (desc) without a full page reload.\n- [ ] Details page renders name, address, star rating, description, amenities, and photo gallery for a valid `:id`.\n- [ ] Requesting an invalid/nonexistent `:id` shows a not-found state, not a crash.\n- [ ] Price breakdown reflects current date range and guest count.\n- [ ] Results page shows a map with a pin per visible result; clicking a pin highlights/scrolls to the matching card.\n- [ ] Hotel details page shows a single-pin map at the hotel's location.\n- [ ] Map failing to load does not block viewing the list/details content.\n- [ ] Hotel details page lists all reviews for that hotel with guest name, rating, text, and date.\n- [ ] Hotel with zero reviews shows an empty state, not a broken list.\n- [ ] Submitting a review with name, rating (1-5), and text creates it via `POST /api/hotels/:id/reviews` and it appears in the list without a full page reload.\n- [ ] Submitting with a missing required field is blocked client-side with a visible validation message.\n- [ ] Submitted review updates the hotel's `averageRating`/`reviewCount`.\n- [ ] Clicking the heart on any hotel card toggles favorited state immediately (optimistic).\n- [ ] Favorited state persists across page reloads via `localStorage`.\n- [ ] Favorite state is consistent between the results list and the details page for the same hotel.\n- [ ] Favorites page lists all hotels currently saved in `localStorage`.\n- [ ] Favorites page shows an empty state with a link back to search when none are saved.\n- [ ] Unfavoriting from the favorites page removes it from the grid immediately.\n- [ ] Changing check-in/check-out dates or guest count on the details page recalculates and displays nights × rate = total.\n- [ ] Guest count exceeding `maxGuests` is blocked with an inline message.\n- [ ] Invalid date range (checkout before/equal to checkin) is blocked with an inline message.\n- [ ] Checkout form requires guest name, email, and mock payment fields before submission is enabled.\n\n\n## Medium Priority\n\n\n## Low Priority\n\n\n## Completed\n- [x] Project enabled for Ralph\n\n## Notes\n- Focus on MVP functionality first\n- Ensure each feature is properly tested\n- Update this file after each major milestone\n","numLines":49,"startLine":1,"totalLines":49}}}
